Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat:=20mobile=20API=20=E2=80=94=20add=20=5Fdis?=
 =?UTF-8?q?play=20fields=20formatted=20per=20System=20Config?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Sweeps the high-traffic mobile endpoints to include *_display variants
of the existing date fields, formatted via School::dateFmt(). The raw
ISO fields are kept as-is for backward compatibility with installed
app builds that do client-side date math.

Endpoints updated (and the new field names):
  /mobile/holidays         → date_display, end_date_display
  /mobile/homework         → due_date_display
  /mobile/diary            → date_display
  /mobile/assignments      → due_date_display
  /mobile/report-cards     → issued_date_display
  /mobile/leaves           → start_date_display, end_date_display
  /mobile/staff-leaves     → start_date_display, end_date_display

Already done in earlier commits:
  /mobile/attendance       → records[].date (formatted)
  /mobile/payments/history → payment_date_display
  /mobile/payments/{id}/receipt → payment_date_display

Mobile screens can read the _display fields directly. Existing screens
keep working with the raw ISO field — they'll just show locale-style
formatting until they're updated to prefer the _display variant in
the next mobile build.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
